This paper deals with the problem of decomposing a data matrix into a low-rank matrix and a sparse component using a convex demixing method. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), information theory (cs.IT), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper provides a theoretical analysis of the proposed method and presents empirical evaluations, which are typical of papers in the above-mentioned sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.IT, cs.NA, and cs.SI.
